    "plan_content": "## PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan\n\nI've studied all 3 reference extensions (IRC, Nostr, Telegram) and the core SDK interfaces. Here's what the plan covers:\n\n---\n\n### Files to create (7 total, all under `extensions/pulseboard/`)\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `package.json` | `@openclaw/pulseboard`, `type: module`, `openclaw` block with channel metadata |\n| `openclaw.plugin.json` | Manifest: `id`, `channels`, minimal `configSchema` |\n| `src/types.ts` | `PulseBoardAccount`, `PulseBoardConfig`, `PulseBoardMessage` interfaces |\n| `src/runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>` → exports `getPulseBoardRuntime`, `setPulseBoardRuntime` |\n| `src/channel.ts` | `createChatChannelPlugin()` with all required adapters; exports `pulseBoardPlugin` |\n| `index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry({ id, name, description, plugin, setRuntime })` |\n| `setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin)` |\n\n### Key design decisions (from research)\n\n- **Outbound shape**: Uses Nostr's \"direct\" pattern (`deliveryMode: \"direct\"` + top-level `sendText`) rather than IRC's \"attached results\" pattern. `sendText` returns `attachChannelToResult(\"pulseboard\", { to, messageId })`.\n- **Runtime type**: `PluginRuntime` imported from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` (matches Telegram pattern).\n- **`index.ts` cast**: `plugin: pulseBoardPlugin as ChannelPlugin` (same as IRC and Telegram).\n- **ID alignment**: `\"pulseboard\"` appears consistently in all 4 locations: `openclaw.plugin.json`, `package.json openclaw.channel.id`, `channel.ts id`, and `index.ts id` — required by repo invariant tests.\n- **`pnpm-workspace.yaml`**: Already includes `extensions/*`, so no workspace registration needed.\n\n### Verification steps\n1. `pnpm tsgo` — type-check imports\n2. `pnpm check` — lint/format\n3. `pnpm build` — check for dynamic import warnings (if needed)",
